1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Paige
2 Craig.
3 WHEREAS, Paige Craig was born on October 10, 1984, in Versailles, Kentucky, to
4 Deen and Pam Pittman Craig; and
5 WHEREAS, Paige Craig graduated from Woodford County High School and was a
6 proud alumna of Jane's School of Dance in Versailles, where she competed in numerous
7 Ohio Dance Masters competitions; and
8 WHEREAS, Paige Craig was a graduate of Eastern Kentucky University and
9 attained a Master of Public Administration degree; and
10 WHEREAS, Paige Craig started her career with the Kentucky State Police in 2012
11 and was a dedicated employee of the Concealed Weapons Section before assuming the
12 role of Missing Persons Clearinghouse Manager in the Intelligence Branch. In this
13 position, Paige Craig oversaw the coordination of efforts to document and locate missing
14 persons at the state level; and
15 WHEREAS, Paige Craig was passionate about her work and led efforts to
16 modernize her agency's approach to missing persons. She was recognized for her efforts
17 and expertise by being invited to Washington, D.C., to take part in an awards ceremony,
18 as well as being asked to conduct missing persons training for both Kentucky State Police
19 cadets and outside groups; and
20 WHEREAS, Paige Craig was selected as the Kentucky state point of contact for the
21 United States Department of Defense Law Enforcement Support Office (LESO), which
22 lends surplus Department of Defense equipment to approximately 160 city and county
23 police agencies across the Commonwealth. In her position as a justice program
24 administrator, Paige Craig oversaw the day-to-day operation of the LESO program
25 statewide; and
26 WHEREAS, Paige Craig was responsible for reviewing and approving equipment
27 requests from agencies, developing state-level policies, and ensuring compliance among
