1 the participating agencies. She once again excelled in her position and was asked to
2 become a member of a national working group that advised the national LESO staff on
3 policies that affected the program nationwide; and
4 WHEREAS, in her time outside of her professional endeavors, Paige Craig enjoyed
5 traveling, Cuban food, and animals; and
6 WHEREAS, Paige Craig passed away on January 21, 2025. In addition to her
7 parents, Paige Craig is survived by her brother, Matthew Craig; her paternal grandfather,
8 Spencer Deen Craig; and a host of friends and loved ones; and
9 WHEREAS, Paige Craig will be deeply missed by all who knew her;
10 NOW, THEREFORE,
11 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
12 Kentucky:
13 Section 1. The Senate hereby expresses its most profound sympathy upon the
14 passing of Paige Craig.
15 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor and loving
16 memory of Paige Craig.
17 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
18 Resolution to Senator Amanda Mays Bledsoe for delivery to the family.
